		"name": "Content Management System",
		"description": "StartFragment\n\n#### **Overview**\n\nThe **Content Management System (CMS) API** is designed to manage **Work Instructions**, **One Point Lessons**, and related factory content. This API allows efficient handling of **products, steps, tools, parts, documents, and media files**.\n\n#### **Key Features**\n\n‚úÖ **Work Instructions Module**\n\n- Manage **Products**, **Steps**, **Tools**, and **Parts**\n    \n- Upload and retrieve **media files (PDFs, images, videos)**\n    \n- Associate **steps with tools and parts**\n    \n\n‚úÖ **One Point Lesson Module**\n\n- **Multilingual support**\n    \n- **Document versioning and control**\n    \n- **Standard and customized document formats**\n    \n- Store metadata like **photo created by, approved by, and date**\n    \n\n‚úÖ **General Features**\n\n- **RESTful API architecture**\n    \n- **JSON-based responses**\n    \n- **File upload support using multipart/form-data**\n    \n- **Real-time content updates**\n    \n\n#### **API Endpoints Overview**\n\nüìå **Work Instructions**\n\n- `POST /products` ‚Üí Create a new product\n    \n- `GET /products` ‚Üí Fetch all products\n    \n- `POST /steps` ‚Üí Create a new step with media\n    \n- `GET /steps/{productId}` ‚Üí Get all steps for a product\n    \n- `POST /tools` ‚Üí Create a new tool\n    \n- `GET /tools` ‚Üí Fetch all tools\n    \n- `POST /parts` ‚Üí Create a new part\n    \n- `GET /parts` ‚Üí Fetch all parts\n    \n\nüìå **One Point Lessons**\n\n- `POST /one-point-lessons` ‚Üí Create a new lesson\n    \n- `GET /one-point-lessons` ‚Üí Fetch all lessons\n    \n- `GET /one-point-lessons/{lessonId}` ‚Üí Get a specific lesson\n    \n\n#### **Usage Instructions**\n\n1Ô∏è‚É£ **Set the Base URL**: Update requests with your **server's IP or domain** (default: `http://localhost:3000`).  \n2Ô∏è‚É£ **Authentication**: No authentication required for basic usage.  \n3Ô∏è‚É£ **File Uploads**: Use `multipart/form-data` for media uploads.  \n4Ô∏è‚É£ **Testing on Postman**: Import this collection and modify parameters accordingly.\n\nüöÄ **For Developers**  \nThis API is structured for **factory use**, ensuring seamless **real-time updates** across multiple worker screens. Developers can easily integrate it into the **frontend system** for better user interaction and content accessibility.\n\nüìå **For More Information**  \nRefer to the API documentation at:  \n[Swagger UI](https://null) (if enabled).\n\nEndFragment",
